# Test Writing Rules

Reference: `work/docs/plans/test_refactoring/TEST_WRITING_GUIDE.md`

## Core Principle
Test what the code DOES, not what it IS.

## Required Patterns
- Test behavior, not property assignment
- Use round-trip JSON: `final restored = Model.fromJson(original.toJson()); expect(restored, equals(original));`
- Always test error handling cases, not just happy path
- Consolidate related checks into comprehensive tests
- Test names must be descriptive and behavior-focused

## Forbidden Patterns
- No constructor-only tests (`expect(obj, isNotNull)`)
- No field-by-field JSON checks (use round-trip instead)
- No trivial null checks without behavior
- No stubs (NEVER acceptable)
- Mocks require explicit justification and approval

## Quality Check
Run `dart run work/scripts/check_test_quality.dart [file]` to verify test quality.
